**Materials and Methods** 

**In silico Analysis of Biosynthetic Gene Clusters (BGCs):** 

To identify, annotate, and analyze potential secondary metabolite biosynthetic gene clusters (BGCs) in Lactococcus lactis, we employed the antiSMASH (**antibiotics & Secondary Metabolite SHalysis**) web server (http://antismash.secondarymetabolites.org/). This bioinformatic pipeline facilitates the rapid detection and characterization of BGCs encompassing all known secondary metabolite classes. 

Following assembly of the Lactococcus lactis genome sequence , the complete sequence was uploaded to the antiSMASH server. The analysis pipeline was set to identify BGCs for all secondary metabolite classes . 

The antiSMASH output provided detailed annotations for predicted BGCs, including: 

● **BGC class:** Classification of the BGC based on the predicted secondary metabolite type 

● **Gene organization:** Identification and organization of genes within the BGC, including core biosynthetic genes and accessory genes 

● **Putative chemical structure prediction:** For NRPS and PKS BGCs, antiSMASH offers in silico prediction of the potential secondary metabolite structure based on the domain organization of the biosynthetic enzymes.
